1
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:14,199
Ini pukul 12 siang di London.

2
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:16,076
Pukul 7 pagi di Philadelphia.

3
00:01:16,117 --> 00:01:19,204
Dan di seluruh dunia,
ini waktunya Live Aid.

4
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:21,623
Wembley menyambut Yang Mulia...

5
00:01:21,664 --> 00:01:24,125
Pangeran dan Putri Wales.

6
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,481
David, lihat aku.

7
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:03,952
Kau melewatkan satu, Paki!

8
00:04:04,869 --> 00:04:06,037
Aku bukan dari Pakistan!

9
00:04:28,727 --> 00:04:30,311
Makan malam siap.

10
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:31,771
Aku tidak lapar, Bu.

11
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:32,981
Mau ke mana?

12
00:04:33,857 --> 00:04:36,067
-Pergi bersama teman.
-Perempuan?

13
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:37,861
Bukan, Bu.

14
00:04:37,902 --> 00:04:39,029
Lihat dirimu.

15
00:04:39,487 --> 00:04:40,822
Cium ibumu.

16
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:46,036
Aku akan pulang terlambat.

17
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:47,537
Kau selalu terlambat.

18
00:04:47,579 --> 00:04:49,831
Hai, Ayah. Bagaimana pekerjaan?

19
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:54,377
Pergi lagi, Farrokh?

20
00:04:54,419 --> 00:04:55,879
Sekarang Freddie, Ayah.

21
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:58,089
Freddie atau Farrokh...

22
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:00,175
apa bedanya jika kau pergi setiap malam...

23
00:05:00,216 --> 00:05:01,885
tanpa memikirkan masa depanmu?

24
00:05:03,511 --> 00:05:06,097
Pikiran baik, kata-kata baik,
perbuatan baik.

25
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:07,974
Seharusnya itu menjadi prinsipmu.

26
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,142
Ya.

27
00:05:09,184 --> 00:05:11,269
Bagaimana hasilnya untuk Ayah?

28
00:05:35,585 --> 00:05:37,504
Mereka lebih bagus dari pekan lalu.

29
00:05:37,545 --> 00:05:39,297
-Mereka keren.
-Ya, lumayan.

30
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:40,340
Ya.

31
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,058
-Pesan apa?
-Segelas bir.

32
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:54,854
-Terima kasih.
-Terima kasih.

33
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:35,770
Sampai jumpa.

34
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:37,939
Humpy Bong?

35
00:06:37,981 --> 00:06:39,274
Humpy Bong.

36
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:41,109
Mereka sukses.
Mereka akan terkenal.

37
00:06:41,151 --> 00:06:43,153
Humpy Bong? Kau bercanda?

38
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:44,320
Jangan lakukan ini, Tim.

39
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:45,488
Maaf, tapi...

40
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:47,323
kita takkan sukses dengan semua ini.

41
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:48,908
Pertunjukan di kampus, bar?

42
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:52,912
Aku harus mencobanya.

43
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:58,960
Kubilang kepadanya, "Kau tak bisa begitu."

44
00:06:59,002 --> 00:07:00,754
Kau tak bisa dengar apa-apa.

45
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,465
Itu menggelikan.

46
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,885
Tapi semua orang memakai
gaun panjang?

47
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:09,012
Aneh sekali.

48
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:14,517
Kau baik-baik saja?

49
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:20,023
Maaf. Aku mencari band tadi.

50
00:07:20,065 --> 00:07:21,691
Biasanya mereka di belakang.

51
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:31,201
Aku suka mantelmu.

52
00:07:34,245 --> 00:07:36,289
Ini dari Biba.

53
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:39,918
Dia bekerja di sana.

54
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:41,670
Terima kasih.

55
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:47,676
Menurutku dia benar.

56
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:49,010
Pertunjukan kita payah.

57
00:07:49,052 --> 00:07:51,680
Kita masih bisa buat kemajuan.

58
00:07:51,721 --> 00:07:54,099
Aku punya urusan lebih penting
untuk Sabtu malam.

59
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:56,226
Aku bisa memberimu nama mereka.

60
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,356
Aku menikmati pertunjukannya.

61
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:03,316
-Terima kasih.
-Terima kasih.

62
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:07,529
Sudah lama aku mengikuti kalian.

63
00:08:08,238 --> 00:08:09,072
Smile.

64
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:12,575
Masuk akal untuk siswa dokter gigi.

65
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:14,828
Dan kau astrofisika, bukan?

66
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:17,247
-Ya.
-Berarti kau yang cerdas di sini.

67
00:08:18,081 --> 00:08:19,582
Kurasa begitu.

68
00:08:19,624 --> 00:08:21,084
Aku belajar desain.

69
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:22,335
-Benarkah?
-Ya.

70
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,921
Aku juga menulis lagu.

71
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:27,632
Mungkin kau berminat.

72
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:30,051
Hanya untuk senang-senang.

73
00:08:30,427 --> 00:08:32,012
Kau terlambat lima menit.

74
00:08:32,386 --> 00:08:34,096
Vokalis utama kami berhenti.

75
00:08:38,058 --> 00:08:39,727
Berarti kau perlu orang baru.

76
00:08:40,102 --> 00:08:41,145
Ada usul?

77
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:45,692
Bagaimana kalau aku?

78
00:08:47,444 --> 00:08:48,737
Tidak dengan gigimu itu.

79
00:08:58,997 --> 00:09:02,751
I know what I'm doin'

80
00:09:03,126 --> 00:09:04,961
I got a feeling

81
00:09:05,003 --> 00:09:09,632
I should be doin' all right

82
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:15,680
Doin' all right

83
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:21,770
Aku lahir dengan tambahan empat gigi seri.

84
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:24,230
Tambah ruang di mulutku
berarti menambah kekuatan suara.

85
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:26,691
Akan kupikirkan tawaranmu.

86
00:09:32,322 --> 00:09:33,365
Bisa main bas?

87
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:35,909
Tidak.

88
00:09:50,173 --> 00:09:51,966
Permisi. Terima kasih.

89
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:56,638
Kau menemukanku.

90
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,431
Bisa kubantu?

91
00:09:58,473 --> 00:10:00,433
Aku suka ini.

92
00:10:00,475 --> 00:10:02,227
Apa ada ukuran untukku?

93
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:05,522
Ini bagian perempuan,
jadi aku tidak tahu pasti.

94
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:09,025
Tidak ada papan nama atau apa pun.

95
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,862
Kurasa itu tidak penting.

96
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:22,038
Mungkin kau suka ini.

97
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:25,041
Kau boleh masuk ruang ini?

98
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:26,084
Tidak juga.

99
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:33,591
Satu lagi.

100
00:10:34,843 --> 00:10:35,927
Boleh?

101
00:10:47,022 --> 00:10:49,190
Penampilanmu eksotis.

102
00:10:51,109 --> 00:10:52,152
Aku suka gayamu.

103
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,655
Menurutku kita harus ambil risiko.

104
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:11,796
Bagaimana menurutmu?

105
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:18,678
Bersulang. Terima kasih.

106
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:20,972
Halo, semuanya.

107
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:25,393
Ada beberapa orang baru.

108
00:11:25,435 --> 00:11:27,020
Ini John Deacon, pemain bas kami.

109
00:11:27,645 --> 00:11:29,773
Dan vokalis baru kami...

110
00:11:29,814 --> 00:11:31,649
Freddie Bul... Bulsara...

111
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,526
Freddie Bulsara.

112
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:35,445
Benar.

113
00:11:35,487 --> 00:11:38,239
Dan Roger, tentu saja.
Anggota yang terpenting.

114
00:11:38,281 --> 00:11:39,574
Hei, Roger!

115
00:11:39,616 --> 00:11:42,369
Halo, orang-orang yang menyenangkan.

116
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:46,581
Di mana Tim?

117
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:49,042
Siapa Paki itu?

118
00:11:49,084 --> 00:11:50,377
Siap, Freddie?

119
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:52,170
Ayo mulai.

120
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,569
Keep yourself alive

121
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:37,465
I was told a million times
Of all the troubles in my way

122
00:12:37,507 --> 00:12:40,760
Mind you grow a little wiser
Little better every day

123
00:12:40,802 --> 00:12:42,429
But if I rode a million rivers

124
00:12:42,929 --> 00:12:44,764
-And I crossed a million miles
-Tidak.

125
00:12:44,806 --> 00:12:46,224
-Still be where I started
-Liriknya salah!

126
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:48,184
-Bread and butter for a smile
-Liriknya salah!

127
00:12:48,226 --> 00:12:51,479
Sold a million mirrors
In shopping alley ways

128
00:12:51,521 --> 00:12:54,774
But I never saw my face
In any window any day

129
00:12:54,816 --> 00:12:56,943
Now they say your folks are telling you

130
00:12:56,985 --> 00:12:58,570
Be a super star

131
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:00,655
Tell you, just be satisfied

132
00:13:00,697 --> 00:13:02,323
And stay right where you are

133
00:13:02,365 --> 00:13:05,910
Keep yourself alive
Keep yourself alive

134
00:13:05,952 --> 00:13:09,414
All you people
Keep yourself alive

135
00:13:11,166 --> 00:13:12,292
Pelajari lagunya, Freddie.

136
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:30,310
SATU TAHUN KEMUDIAN

137
00:13:43,948 --> 00:13:44,991
Kau terlambat.

138
00:13:50,455 --> 00:13:51,539
Ini omong kosong!

139
00:13:56,002 --> 00:13:58,963
Berlawanan arah jarum jam, John.

140
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:00,715
Masa? Terima kasih, Brian.

141
00:14:00,757 --> 00:14:02,467
Kau mau coba? Silakan.

142
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:03,468
Tidak. Kau sudah bagus.

143
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:06,805
Tiket kita terjual habis di semua bar
dan universitas di selatan Glasgow...

144
00:14:06,846 --> 00:14:10,016
dan aku terjebak entah di mana,
makan roti lapis daging!

145
00:14:10,058 --> 00:14:12,185
Kita tidak berpikir cukup luas.

146
00:14:12,435 --> 00:14:13,853
Apa yang kau pikirkan, Fred?

147
00:14:13,895 --> 00:14:14,938
Sebuah album.

148
00:14:14,979 --> 00:14:16,898
Kita tak mampu membuat album.

149
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:18,566
Kita akan temukan caranya.

150
00:14:20,610 --> 00:14:22,320
Berapa harga mobil ini?

151
00:14:24,114 --> 00:14:25,907
Kuharap kau bercanda.

152
00:14:28,326 --> 00:14:29,703
Itu penghasilan tiga bulan.

153
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:31,037
Dan mobil yang bagus.

154
00:14:31,079 --> 00:14:32,831
Jangan dramatis, sayang.

155
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:35,750
Kau merekam album malam ini.
Ayo!

156
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:45,010
-Suaraku jelek?
-Tidak, bagus.

157
00:14:45,343 --> 00:14:47,303
-Boleh coba lagi?
-Tentu.

158
00:14:48,138 --> 00:14:49,264
Tentu, ini uangmu.

159
00:14:49,806 --> 00:14:50,807
Sungguhan.

160
00:15:01,151 --> 00:15:03,611
-Jauh lebih baik.
-Kita perlu bereksperimen.

161
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:08,074
Coba gerakkan ke kiri kanan
untuk ah-ah-ah.

162
00:15:15,248 --> 00:15:16,958
Di tengah untuk penutup.

163
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,376
Lalu habisi!

164
00:15:18,418 --> 00:15:19,419
Ya!

165
00:15:26,259 --> 00:15:27,177
Itu bagus, bukan?

166
00:15:30,847 --> 00:15:32,390
Ada waktu untuk tambah beberapa lagi?

167
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:35,101
Studio buka pukul 8.00,
jadi kita punya 30 menit lagi.

168
00:15:45,612 --> 00:15:46,780
-Kedengarannya bagus.
-Itu bagus.

169
00:15:55,747 --> 00:15:57,665
RT, siapa anak-anak di dalam?

170
00:15:57,707 --> 00:16:01,628
Band pelajar yang melakukan hal-hal aneh.

171
00:16:01,670 --> 00:16:03,088
Punya demo lagunya?

172
00:16:03,129 --> 00:16:04,589
Kita begadang semalaman.

173
00:16:15,558 --> 00:16:17,143
Nama barunya adalah Queen?

174
00:16:17,644 --> 00:16:19,187
Seperti "Yang Mulia."

175
00:16:19,229 --> 00:16:21,064
Karena ini memukau...

176
00:16:21,106 --> 00:16:23,900
dan tak ada yang lebih memukau
dari aku.

177
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:34,244
Ini ranjang yang paling tidak praktis.

178
00:16:45,505 --> 00:16:47,090
Itu indah.

179
00:16:59,936 --> 00:17:01,938
Punya potensi.

180
00:17:11,948 --> 00:17:14,284
-Aku harus pergi bekerja.
-Tidak boleh.

181
00:17:14,325 --> 00:17:16,077
Kau akan menafkahiku
jika aku dipecat?

182
00:17:17,412 --> 00:17:19,289
Aku akan selalu menjagamu.

183
00:17:19,664 --> 00:17:21,041
Nanti aku...

184
00:17:21,082 --> 00:17:22,584
Nanti aku terlambat.

185
00:17:34,763 --> 00:17:36,222
Kau cantik sekali.

186
00:17:46,441 --> 00:17:47,567
Ketika aku kecil...

187
00:17:47,609 --> 00:17:50,904
aku suka berlarian di rumah
dan bersembunyi...

188
00:17:51,404 --> 00:17:52,280
dia tak bisa menemukanku.

189
00:17:54,199 --> 00:17:55,200
Gadis pintar.

190
00:17:56,993 --> 00:17:59,287
-Bilang ke ayahmu aku senang bertemu dia.
-Sudah.

191
00:17:59,329 --> 00:18:01,998
Bilang terima kasih
untuk kue ulang tahunnya.

192
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:03,249
Sudah.

193
00:18:04,042 --> 00:18:07,045
Bilang anaknya sangat seksi.

194
00:18:08,129 --> 00:18:10,298
Freddie, dia bisa baca gerak bibir.

195
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:12,717
Mary...

196
00:18:12,759 --> 00:18:15,553
entah sudah berapa lama
aku menunggu Farrokh...

197
00:18:15,595 --> 00:18:17,263
mengajak pulang gadis baik sepertimu.

198
00:18:17,305 --> 00:18:18,473
Farrokh?

199
00:18:18,515 --> 00:18:21,184
Farrokh tidak bilang
dia lahir di Zanzibar?

200
00:18:21,226 --> 00:18:23,269
Tidak.

201
00:18:23,311 --> 00:18:24,729
-Dulu ada gadis bernama Zanzibari.
-Tunggu.

202
00:18:24,771 --> 00:18:26,648
Kupikir Freddie lahir di London.

203
00:18:26,690 --> 00:18:29,067
-Memang. Pada usia 18.
-Diam.

204
00:18:29,109 --> 00:18:30,860
Keluarga kami Parsi India.

205
00:18:30,902 --> 00:18:32,821
-Ibu. Ibu, Ibu.
-Mary...

206
00:18:32,862 --> 00:18:33,988
-Ibu.
-Ibu, kumohon...

207
00:18:34,030 --> 00:18:35,323
Ini. Coba lihat.

208
00:18:35,365 --> 00:18:36,783
-Ya.
-Kumohon!

209
00:18:36,825 --> 00:18:38,159
-Ayo.
-Kita harus melihatnya.

210
00:18:38,827 --> 00:18:42,872
Seribu tahun lalu,
kaum Parsi kabur ke India dari Persia...

211
00:18:42,914 --> 00:18:44,416
menghindari penganiayaan Muslim.

212
00:18:44,457 --> 00:18:46,668
Benarkah? Itu buruk.

213
00:18:46,710 --> 00:18:48,086
Kenapa kau pergi dari Zanzibar?

214
00:18:48,128 --> 00:18:49,337
Kami tidak pergi.

215
00:18:49,379 --> 00:18:50,505
Dia begitu kecil.

216
00:18:50,547 --> 00:18:52,674
Kami diusir
dengan hanya membawa pakaian.

217
00:18:52,716 --> 00:18:54,676
Dia petinju yang baik.

218
00:18:55,844 --> 00:18:57,178
Terpaksa.

219
00:18:57,220 --> 00:18:59,556
Lawannya selalu ingin
meninju masuk giginya.

220
00:19:00,598 --> 00:19:01,808
Jelas sebuah sasaran.

221
00:19:01,850 --> 00:19:04,728
Berapa usianya di foto ini?

222
00:19:04,769 --> 00:19:06,646
-Tiga atau empat tahun.
-Sudah bertinju?

223
00:19:06,688 --> 00:19:07,647
Luar biasa.

224
00:19:10,483 --> 00:19:11,401
Mercury?

225
00:19:12,235 --> 00:19:13,236
Tidak melihat ke belakang.

226
00:19:13,945 --> 00:19:15,196
Hanya ke depan.

227
00:19:15,238 --> 00:19:17,157
Kini nama keluarga
tidak cukup baik untukmu?

228
00:19:17,198 --> 00:19:18,658
Itu hanya nama panggung.

229
00:19:18,908 --> 00:19:20,869
Tidak.

230
00:19:22,078 --> 00:19:23,496
Aku resmi mengubahnya.

231
00:19:23,538 --> 00:19:25,540
Aku punya paspor baru dan lainnya.

232
00:19:27,709 --> 00:19:29,127
Kash, berapa usiamu di sini?

233
00:19:29,169 --> 00:19:30,003
Entahlah.

234
00:19:30,045 --> 00:19:31,880
Itu sebelum Freddie ke sekolah asrama.

235
00:19:31,921 --> 00:19:34,591
Kukirim Farrokh ke asrama
agar menjadi Parsi yang baik.

236
00:19:34,632 --> 00:19:35,967
Dia terlalu liar dan sulit diatur.

237
00:19:36,009 --> 00:19:37,344
Tapi apa hasilnya?

238
00:19:37,385 --> 00:19:40,096
Pikiran baik, kata-kata baik,
perbuatan baik.

239
00:19:42,891 --> 00:19:44,976
Kau takkan berhasil
jika berpura-pura jadi orang lain.

240
00:19:45,018 --> 00:19:46,686
Ada yang mau kue?

241
00:19:47,729 --> 00:19:49,397
Kue selalu enak.

242
00:19:49,439 --> 00:19:50,440
Halo?

243
00:19:50,482 --> 00:19:51,858
Sebentar.

244
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:52,859
Freddie Mercury.

245
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:55,070
Telepon untukmu.

246
00:19:55,111 --> 00:19:56,696
Aku suka nama itu.

247
00:19:56,738 --> 00:19:59,783
Freddie bilang kau semacam ilmuwan.

248
00:19:59,824 --> 00:20:01,534
